ROXBURY MEAL ORDER UPDATE 09/10/20:

Due to the overwhelming response from our Roxbury families requesting free meals, we will only deliver meals to our Free & Reduced families. Free & Reduced families do not have to fill out the weekly form.

All other families will need to pick up meals for their children at their home school daily. The meal ordering form has been revised and includes the pickup times at the respective schools. Each school’s form can be found at www.roxbury.org/Page/54.

Families who would like to apply for Free & Reduced meals can do so in Genesis at any point throughout the year.

post_text:
HONEYWELL FROM SUPERINTENDENT RADULIC 09/06/20:

Dear Roxbury Families:

We are aware of the inconsistency of the rSchoolToday app and share your frustration. Please know that we are continuing to work with the company to resolve the integration issue. If for any reason we are not able to complete the integration process, I will send out a correspondence with the alternative option for health screenings by tomorrow at 5 p.m.

If necessary, our contingency plan will be a Google Form link that will be posted on the district webpage for your convenience with our hotline as a secondary option. Please be assured that whatever happens, you will have the ability to provide a health screening for your child before tomorrow evening in preparation for the first day of school on Tuesday.

We sincerely apologize for any inconvenience and truly appreciate your patience. Enjoy your Labor Day.

SEPTEMBER RE-OPENING UPDATE 09/04/20:

The USDA announced that it would be extending the free meals for all families regardless of free/reduced status thru the end of December whether you are in-person or virtual.

Families do not have to apply for these free meals through Dec 2020. However, meal request forms will need to be completed daily. These links are available at https://www.roxbury.org/Page/54. Orders must be submitted by no later than 8:00 a.m. the morning of to guarantee delivery.

Families interested in receiving free and reduced meals in January 2021, will need to apply prior to December 31st in Genesis.

Roxbury Schools is accepting 2020/2021 Kindergarten registrations for the coming school year.

Children must be five years old on or before October 1, 2020 to participate. To register for Kindergarten, parents must bring their child’s original birth certificate, a record of immunizations, and three proofs of residency at the time of registration. To begin the pre-registration process and for additional information, please visit www.roxbury.org/KindergartenRegistration. Families will be contacted via email by their child’s school once the pre-registration process has been started.

Not sure what school your child should be attending? Contact Transportation at 973-584-6756.

post_text: It is with sad news that we share the passing of former RHS band instructor, Darryl Bott.
shared_text:
Rutgers University Marching Band
May 24 at 10:29 AM ·

The Marching Scarlet Knights are saddened to pass along the news that Professor Darryl Bott passed away last night after a very heroic year and half long battle with cancer.

Professor Bott taught at Rutgers for 15 years and served in many capacities, including Director of Bands and Assistant Chair of the Music Department. In addition, he contributed nearly 30 years of dedicated teaching and service to the public schools of NJ.

Professor Bott was a dear friend and colleague and will be greatly missed by many of his students and colleagues. He had an unrelenting vision for the Rutgers Band Program and truly believed in what can and will be achieved at our prestigious university.

Our thoughts and prayers are certainly with his family and friends during this most difficult time.

Roxbury Schools continues Kindergarten registration for the upcoming school year during the COVID-19 school closures.

Children must be five years old on or before October 1, 2020 to participate. To register for Kindergarten, parents must bring their child’s original birth certificate, a record of immunizations, and three proofs of residency at the time of registration. To begin the pre-registration process and for additional information, please visit www.roxbury.org/KindergartenRegistration. Families will be contacted via email by their child’s school once the pre-registration process has been started.

Not sure what school your child should be attending? Contact Transportation at 973-584-6756.

Other non-food items being collected include Liquid Dish Soap, Diapers (Size 3), Paper Towels, and Conditioner

shared_text:
Roxbury Township, New Jersey
April 23 at 2:35 PM ·

The Roxbury Township Mayor and Council have announced that on Tuesday, April 28, 2020, the Township will host the Table of Hope Mobile Food Pantry for their Mobile Food Drop, beginning at 10:30 am until 12:00 pm in the Horseshoe Lake Park parking lot, located on Eyland Avenue. Mayor Bob DeFillippo said, “in this time of great need, the Table of Hope Program is another way the Township is responding to help residents.” Pastor Sidney Williams, volunteers from Morris Habitat for Humanity, and Roxbury Township volunteers will be placing bags of food into trunks of residents in need. There are no income guidelines or pre-registration requirements to participate. As a reminder, in order to maintain proper social distancing, those who attend must drive up to get in line. Please do not get out of your car; food will be placed in your trunk. Make sure you follow the directions of the Roxbury Police Department who will be directing traffic. For more information on this event, please call (973)448-2000.

2020 Census | United States Census Bureau

Morris County Government
April 1 at 10:02 AM ·

Happy April 1 - it's Census Day!

Now, more than ever, we need you to fill out the Census! This simple survey, held once every 10 years, is critical to ensure federal funding continues to flow to Morris County.

Census data helps to fund healthcare, education, transportation, and other critical services.

Stand up and be counted - fill out the census today!

post_text: Our staff continues to support our students during these unprecedented times. Check out these resources compiled by Mrs. Caivano. #FlexibleInstructionDays
shared_text:
ROXBURY.ORG
Media Center / Overview

Roxana Russo Caivano shared a link to the group: ROXBURY SCHOOLS PARENT GROUP.
March 20 at 9:32 AM ·

I see some posts about educational sites to visit, and I just wanted to let all the parents out there know that I've been compiling lists of just that. As the HS Librarian, I've been focusing on the older kids, but I have added elementary resources as well, and I will continue to add as I find more. Please check it out, and if any of your kids need help with anything, feel free to reach out to me or any of the other fabulous Librarians in our district. Click on the Flexible Instruction link and navigate to Online Educational Resources. There are tabs for Arts, Cultural, and Elementary. But have your kids check out the whole site, there's lots of research help and ways to get eBooks as well. Hope everyone is coping through these tough times! I'm at rcaivano@roxbury.org

For greater detail, please see Superintendent Radulic's correspondence at www.roxbury.org and join a live presentation of our Flexible Instructional Day at 10am this morning. The link to join can also be found on our district webpage.

Thank you and be safe, Roxbury.

The Roxbury STEAM Expo is TODAY at EMS from 9 a.m. to 1:30 p.m. Come check out more than 100 student-created sustainable themed projects focused on Seeds of Sustainability: Healthy Minds, Healthy Bodies.

We will also have different vendors and groups promoting STEAM and Sustainability-related themes like the Morris County MUA, Roxbury Clean Communities, The Girl Scout STAR Lab and Squishy Circuitry, Home Depot, Raritan Headwaters Association, NJ Clean Energy, Amy Rubin from Mindfulselff, RoNetco, Maschio's, The Art Diner, and more! Be sure to stop by to check them all out!

HONEYWELL ANNOUNCEMENT 03/02/20:

Good afternoon, Roxbury families. This is Loretta Radulic, your Superintendent of Schools, with some valuable information. Please check the district website at www.roxbury.org for my correspondence regarding the Coronavirus.

Also, at this evening's Board of Education meeting, there are three important presentations: 1) Osmo as an Instructional Tool, 2) Social Emotional Learning in our district, and 3) a presentation on the 2021-2022 school year calendar.

We hope you will join us. Have a great afternoon.

Sent By: Loretta Radulic, Superintendent of Schools

Dear Roxbury Families,

To help support our community in this sad time, Eisenhower Middle School will be open today, February 14th from 8 a.m. to 3:00 p.m. Counseling and support services will be made available on site to all Roxbury students and families.

In addition to this shared document, resources will be posted on the district website and also be made available to those who visit Eisenhower throughout the day. We encourage you to utilize these resources for yourself and your child.

Additional counselors will be made available in the coming days and weeks to support our students and community through this challenging time.

Please feel free to contact the school office or one of the school's mental health professionals if your child is in need of additional assistance.

post_text:
ROXBURY SCHOOLS - Important Announcement 02/13/20

Dear Roxbury Families,

It is with deep sadness and with the family's permission, that I share that Maya Guberman, an 8th grade student at Eisenhower Middle School passed away with morning. I am asking that you respect the privacy of the family, but keep them in your kind thoughts. Know that we have been working with administration and staff to share resources available to our students. From you, parents, we ask that you please pay attention to your children's reactions.

To help support our community in this sad time, Eisenhower Middle School will be open tomorrow beginning at 8am with counselors available to our children and their families.

Thank you.

Loretta Radulic, Superintendent of Schools.

From you, parents, we ask that you please pay attention to your children's reactions.

post_text:
Roxbury HS Cross Country team competed in the North 1 Group 3 Sectional Championships last weekend. The Boys team placed 4th overall advancing the entire team to the Group 3 State Championships. Juniors Nate Hajel and Thomas Schulz placed 2nd and 6th respectively.

The Girls team placed 6th overall and advance senior, Lauren Tom (14th) and freshman, Gabby Daskalova (7th) to represent at the Group 3 State Championships.

The Group 3 State Championships will be contested at Holmdel Park this Saturday, November 16th #GoGaelsGo #RoxburyPride
